gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: This feature class contains lines that represent the Public Land Survey (PLS) for Ramsey County Minnesota. In 1985, the county began a 5 year project to modernize it's land records mapping system. The PLS layer would serve as the foundation of a computerized Land Information System. As part of the project, the County developed an accurate coordinate control base for the LIS. In mid to late 1980's , 27 existing State and Federal first order accuracy positions in Ramsey County were densified by a GPS (Global Positioning System) Network of 171 second order accuracy positions. These positions were established and recorded on existing public land survey corner monuments and accessory monuments through out the county.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: The section lines in this data set support many functions including thematic mapping, asset management, property assessment, surveying and engineering projects.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Data was created as part of a 5 year project to modernize the land records mapping system.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Information is visually inspected and corrected as necessary.
Attributes held within the GIS graphical database are manually entered by GIS personnel. There are check plots produced to verify information.
Positional accuracy is second order. Positions are generally ground truthed to less than 0.10 feet.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: PROCEDURE: This layer contains line positions derived form first order accuracy State & Federal positions, second order accuracy GPS positions and electronic total station (ETS) field traverse data. PROJECTION: Ramsey County Coordinate System
